The paper discusses a novel approach to co-adapt a robot morphology and its controller using deep reinforcement learning, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The use of deep reinforcement learning also suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the possibility of applying the approach to real-world robot designs, indicating a potential interest in systems and control (cs.SY) and computer vision (cs.CV) for perception and sensing.
